<item>
            <title>[LU-12805] replay-single/36 is broken</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12805</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;replay-single/36 seem to be very old, written at times of CFS when all tests were local:&lt;br/&gt;
	if $LCTL dk | grep &quot;stale lock .*cookie&quot;; then&lt;br/&gt;
		error &quot;cancel after replay failed&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
i.e. it checks for server-side messages on the client.&lt;br/&gt;
I noticed that having it failing constantly locally. then tried to change so that server side&apos;s lock is grepped: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/36127/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/36127/&lt;/a&gt; &amp;#8211; all testing sessions failed in autotest.&lt;br/&gt;
AFAIU, ELC is the root cause - it packs cancels, then client doesn&apos;t replay cancelled locks but the original pack is sent anyway.&lt;br/&gt;
I think we should disable 36 at least.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
